00:33:23,450 --> 00:33:24,650
I know you're hungry.

572
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:27,330
Here you go.

573
00:33:27,420 --> 00:33:28,600
Why are you here?

574
00:33:29,540 --> 00:33:30,780
What do you think?

575
00:33:31,090 --> 00:33:33,180
You're getting too bold now.

576
00:33:34,380 --> 00:33:35,780
A helpless girl like you,

577
00:33:35,860 --> 00:33:37,800
coming to a strange place like this,

578
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:39,050
looking for a stranger.

579
00:33:39,050 --> 00:33:40,900
Don't you know it's dangerous?

580
00:33:41,170 --> 00:33:43,430
Come on, I know how
to take care of myself.

581
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:45,170
Aren't you afraid?

582
00:33:45,260 --> 00:33:46,360
Aren't you?

583
00:33:46,610 --> 00:33:48,530
What if Zhang Si suddenly shows up

584
00:33:48,620 --> 00:33:49,800
and drags you inside?

585
00:33:49,800 --> 00:33:52,110
How can you resist?

586
00:33:53,140 --> 00:33:55,070
Just cut it out.

587
00:33:58,660 --> 00:34:00,120
Let's play a game.

588
00:34:01,020 --> 00:34:02,550
You're scared, aren't you?

589
00:34:03,090 --> 00:34:05,420
Trying to distract yourself
with a game, are you?

590
00:34:05,420 --> 00:34:06,600
Then forget it.

591
00:34:06,690 --> 00:34:08,989
What game do you want to play?

592
00:34:09,219 --> 00:34:11,639
Ever heard of "one-two-three-three"?

593
00:34:11,730 --> 00:34:13,199
What game is that?

594
00:34:13,420 --> 00:34:14,520
Like this.

595
00:34:15,420 --> 00:34:17,370
Who doesn't know that?

596
00:34:17,460 --> 00:34:18,440
I'll win.

597
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:19,920
I'm sure.

598
00:34:30,610 --> 00:34:31,710
You lose.

599
00:34:32,699 --> 00:34:33,800
What's that?

600
00:34:35,940 --> 00:34:37,000
You're cheating.

601
00:34:37,090 --> 00:34:38,190
Stop cheating.

602
00:34:38,320 --> 00:34:39,600
This is cheating.

603
00:34:52,139 --> 00:34:53,900
I wonder when Zhang Si will be back?

604
00:34:53,900 --> 00:34:55,360
It's been a day.

605
00:35:06,460 --> 00:35:07,790
He's still not back yet.

606
00:35:09,380 --> 00:35:14,300
♫ Chasing unfinished
dreams, even if I fall down ♫

607
00:35:15,460 --> 00:35:19,020
♫ Time never goes back ♫

608
00:35:19,570 --> 00:35:22,290
♫ Stubborn but comforting ♫

609
00:35:22,380 --> 00:35:25,270
♫ Right beside you ♫

610
00:35:25,570 --> 00:35:28,330
♫ Following closely like a shadow ♫

611
00:35:28,420 --> 00:35:30,120
That was beautiful.

612
00:35:30,860 --> 00:35:33,260
You should've heard me
before I made it big.

613
00:35:33,290 --> 00:35:35,270
When I was a trainee,

614
00:35:35,570 --> 00:35:37,440
I used to hole up in the studio

615
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:39,250
and practise for the whole day.

616
00:35:39,250 --> 00:35:40,880
I was tired and lonely.

617
00:35:42,660 --> 00:35:43,780
I don't miss it.

618
00:35:44,290 --> 00:35:45,540
I know how you feel.

619
00:35:45,650 --> 00:35:47,760
When I started out as a streamer,

620
00:35:47,850 --> 00:35:49,960
I would be alone in the streaming room

621
00:35:50,050 --> 00:35:52,200
facing only a handful of fans.

622
00:35:53,660 --> 00:35:55,550
The loneliness was unbearable.

623
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:58,840
Is it more tiring

624
00:35:58,940 --> 00:36:00,370
to be a streamer

625
00:36:00,460 --> 00:36:02,200
or a CEO?

626
00:36:02,860 --> 00:36:05,350
Being a streamer is a solo act.

627
00:36:05,490 --> 00:36:08,540
But as a CEO, you're stretched
on all sides.

628
00:36:08,940 --> 00:36:11,200
There are too many things
to think about.

629
00:36:11,770 --> 00:36:14,090
Actually, it's not easy

630
00:36:14,180 --> 00:36:15,440
to do everything well.

631
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:20,660
Look.

632
00:36:20,940 --> 00:36:22,670
Look at all the people fishing.

633
00:36:23,940 --> 00:36:25,040
Look over there.

634
00:36:25,140 --> 00:36:26,480
The lights on the bridge

635
00:36:26,570 --> 00:36:28,970
and the lights on the boat
are so beautiful.

636
00:36:29,660 --> 00:36:30,760
Yes indeed.

637
00:36:31,860 --> 00:36:33,220
These lights will eventually

638
00:36:33,220 --> 00:36:35,640
be turned off at night.

639
00:36:36,980 --> 00:36:38,460
Just like streamers.

640
00:36:40,090 --> 00:36:42,330
In truth, a streamer can only work

641
00:36:42,420 --> 00:36:43,740
for so many years.

642
00:36:44,010 --> 00:36:47,700
From a rookie to the top performer,

643
00:36:48,140 --> 00:36:50,720
an enormous effort is required

644
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,560
for growth and breakthrough.

645
00:36:52,650 --> 00:36:53,880
I had no idea

646
00:36:53,970 --> 00:36:55,290
how tough I had to be

647
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:57,360
in order to survive the journey.

648
00:37:00,010 --> 00:37:01,110
Xi Xi.

649
00:37:01,620 --> 00:37:02,880
You're amazing.

650
00:37:05,250 --> 00:37:06,350
Really?

651
00:37:30,940 --> 00:37:33,510
Miss, isn't this something?

652
00:37:38,620 --> 00:37:39,720
What do you think?

653
00:37:39,810 --> 00:37:41,120
Are you thirsty?

654
00:37:43,170 --> 00:37:44,400
I'll open it for you.

655
00:37:46,420 --> 00:37:49,880
You even know my favourite
drink is Peach and Pink Grapefruit.

656
00:37:49,970 --> 00:37:51,270
Look,

657
00:37:51,650 --> 00:37:56,700
I got you your favourite food and drink.

658
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:59,450
Aren't you going to let
me in on some information?

659
00:37:59,450 --> 00:38:01,310
Tell me where she went.

660
00:38:01,650 --> 00:38:03,160
You've angered her,

661
00:38:03,250 --> 00:38:05,790
and you expect me to sell out
my sworn sister

662
00:38:06,040 --> 00:38:07,700
for a little supper?

663
00:38:07,980 --> 00:38:10,160
I couldn't find her anywhere.

664
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:11,970
She didn't even answer my call.

665
00:38:11,980 --> 00:38:13,080
I'm anxious.

666
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:14,640
Now you know.

667
00:38:14,730 --> 00:38:15,990
Why were you mad at her?

668
00:38:16,050 --> 00:38:17,150
I...

669
00:38:17,930 --> 00:38:19,440
I was wrong, okay?

670
00:38:19,530 --> 00:38:21,080
Tell me where she is.

671
00:38:26,410 --> 00:38:27,880
She's with Jiang Zhe Yang.

672
00:38:29,180 --> 00:38:30,280
What?

673
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:34,840
She's with Jiang Zhe Yang.

674
00:38:38,810 --> 00:38:41,230
She's with Jiang Zhe Yang?

675
00:38:41,530 --> 00:38:43,950
She's with Jiang Zhe Yang?

676
00:38:44,860 --> 00:38:46,130
She came here just now.

677
00:38:46,210 --> 00:38:47,980
Then Jiang Zhe Yang called her.

678
00:38:48,140 --> 00:38:50,130
As you know, he is our company's

679
00:38:50,220 --> 00:38:52,000
main breadwinner.

680
00:38:52,090 --> 00:38:54,080
So they went out for a talk.

681
00:38:54,800 --> 00:38:57,330
Isn't it night time now?

682
00:38:57,420 --> 00:38:58,370
Is there a need

683
00:38:58,460 --> 00:39:00,160
to talk at this time?

684
00:39:00,250 --> 00:39:01,770
What's there to talk about?

685
00:39:01,770 --> 00:39:03,140
Isn't it time to come home?

686
00:39:03,140 --> 00:39:04,240
Isn't it late now?

687
00:39:04,330 --> 00:39:05,860
Don't they know the time now?

688
00:39:05,860 --> 00:39:07,110
Can't she talk to me?

689
00:39:09,700 --> 00:39:10,960
Are you both together?

690
00:39:10,970 --> 00:39:12,070
No.

691
00:39:12,700 --> 00:39:13,960
So what's the big deal?

692
00:39:14,420 --> 00:39:16,610
They're both singles.

693
00:39:16,690 --> 00:39:18,330
What's wrong with a meetup

694
00:39:18,420 --> 00:39:19,520
or even a date?

695
00:39:19,620 --> 00:39:21,130
A date?

696
00:39:21,220 --> 00:39:22,920
They have nothing in common.

697
00:39:23,010 --> 00:39:24,140
You must be kidding.

698
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:27,460
Since when are you two together?

699
00:39:27,460 --> 00:39:28,670
We are not.

700
00:39:29,090 --> 00:39:31,850
It can't be more than a month.

701
00:39:31,940 --> 00:39:33,620
Otherwise, I would have known it

702
00:39:33,620 --> 00:39:34,990
from her expression.

703
00:39:35,420 --> 00:39:36,940
Who made the first move?

704
00:39:37,570 --> 00:39:40,570
Since she's so proud and awkward,

705
00:39:40,660 --> 00:39:42,920
it must be you who confessed to her?

706
00:39:43,010 --> 00:39:44,200
I didn't confess.

707
00:39:44,290 --> 00:39:45,240
How did you do it?

708
00:39:45,330 --> 00:39:47,440
Just tell me.

709
00:39:47,610 --> 00:39:48,710
Let's see.

710
00:39:51,050 --> 00:39:53,130
Yes, that's the expression.

711
00:39:53,210 --> 00:39:55,010
You were blushing, weren't you?

712
00:39:55,080 --> 00:39:56,630
I didn't blush.

713
00:39:57,570 --> 00:39:58,680
What did you say?

714
00:39:59,370 --> 00:40:00,770
Let me analyse it for you.

715
00:40:00,860 --> 00:40:03,120
I didn't say anything. I didn't confess.

716
00:40:03,210 --> 00:40:04,750
What was her response?

717
00:40:06,970 --> 00:40:08,200
Stop asking.

718
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:10,090
-She...
-Just stop.

719
00:40:10,170 --> 00:40:12,180
-She won't like it.
-Confessed together?

720
00:40:12,180 --> 00:40:14,400
I'm sure you made the confession first.

721
00:40:17,700 --> 00:40:19,770
Eat this and shut up.

722
00:40:19,850 --> 00:40:21,230
You said too much.

723
00:40:22,040 --> 00:40:23,140
Look at that.

724
00:40:23,290 --> 00:40:24,420
The waterfall looks fun.

725
00:40:24,420 --> 00:40:26,490
-Yes, I noticed.
-There's a smiley face.

726
00:40:26,490 --> 00:40:27,840
Happy Children's Day,

727
00:40:28,850 --> 00:40:30,030
little kid.

728
00:40:30,330 --> 00:40:31,750
You're a little kid.

729
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:35,670
[JUKEBOX]

730
00:40:32,370 --> 00:40:34,040
That guy sure looks like you.

731
00:40:34,130 --> 00:40:35,870
-Who's that?
-That's me.

732
00:40:35,780 --> 00:40:45,350
["Dui Dao", Jiang Zhe Yang]

733
00:40:36,490 --> 00:40:38,030
It really is you.

734
00:40:38,620 --> 00:40:39,530
"Dui Diao".

735
00:40:39,620 --> 00:40:41,550
What a weird name.

736
00:40:41,700 --> 00:40:43,280
That's "Dui Dao" to you.

737
00:40:43,370 --> 00:40:45,150
-Dui Diao?
-Dui Dao!

738
00:40:48,380 --> 00:40:49,310
Let me be honest.

739
00:40:49,380 --> 00:40:50,640
The photo is overdone.

740
00:40:50,700 --> 00:40:51,850
You look better in person.

741
00:40:51,850 --> 00:40:53,090
Really? Then I'll ask them

742
00:40:53,090 --> 00:40:54,820
to change the poster tomorrow.

743
00:40:55,250 --> 00:40:56,440
It's not necessary.

744
00:40:56,530 --> 00:40:58,390
The edited photo is not bad at all.

745
00:41:00,140 --> 00:41:01,680
We're ex-classmates,

746
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:04,470
yet I've never listened
to any of your albums.

747
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:06,440
Would you like to?

748
00:41:07,860 --> 00:41:08,990
Sure.

749
00:41:10,420 --> 00:41:11,520
Wait.

750
00:41:13,570 --> 00:41:15,100
What are you trying to find?

751
00:41:20,980 --> 00:41:23,480
This is the key to the shop.

752
00:41:23,570 --> 00:41:25,290
A buddy of mine owns this bar.

753
00:41:25,380 --> 00:41:27,230
He hides the key here.

754
00:41:27,810 --> 00:41:28,910
Here.

755
00:41:30,090 --> 00:41:31,460
Back up.

756
00:41:31,660 --> 00:41:32,890
It isn't a good idea

757
00:41:32,980 --> 00:41:34,400
to just sneak in, is it?

758
00:41:34,700 --> 00:41:35,680
It's no big deal.

759
00:41:35,760 --> 00:41:37,160
We're not thieves.

760
00:41:37,250 --> 00:41:38,530
Are you a thief?

761
00:41:38,610 --> 00:41:39,570
Neither am I.

762
00:41:39,660 --> 00:41:40,990
It's all right, come on.

763
00:41:41,130 --> 00:41:42,270
It's my buddy.

764
00:41:45,810 --> 00:41:46,950
After you.

765
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:49,070
My first time breaking into a bar.

766
00:41:57,900 --> 00:41:59,960
There are so many vinyl records here.

767
00:42:00,010 --> 00:42:02,960
You said it. This floor is the bar.

768
00:42:03,040 --> 00:42:05,880
The second floor is where
you listen to records.

769
00:42:05,980 --> 00:42:07,950
Come with me.

770
00:42:15,660 --> 00:42:17,270
Do you see that?

771
00:42:18,420 --> 00:42:19,400
So many albums?

772
00:42:19,490 --> 00:42:20,590
Yes.

773
00:42:21,970 --> 00:42:23,160
Is this yours?

774
00:42:24,090 --> 00:42:25,880
-Yes.
-It's "Dui Diao".

775
00:42:25,980 --> 00:42:29,020
No. This is "Zhe", another album.

776
00:42:29,490 --> 00:42:30,980
You've released so many albums.

777
00:42:30,980 --> 00:42:32,080
Yes.

778
00:42:38,690 --> 00:42:39,790
Jia Yun.

779
00:42:41,090 --> 00:42:43,090
Why aren't you surprised at all

780
00:42:43,180 --> 00:42:44,790
with Xi Xi and I?

781
00:42:48,690 --> 00:42:49,900
I've been rooting for you two

782
00:42:49,900 --> 00:42:51,780
since way back in university.

783
00:42:52,050 --> 00:42:53,370
All these years,

784
00:42:53,460 --> 00:42:55,160
I've been fantasizing about

785
00:42:55,250 --> 00:42:56,580
you two being together.

786
00:42:56,980 --> 00:42:59,150
Now my dream has finally come true.

787
00:43:00,010 --> 00:43:01,400
"Back in university"?

788
00:43:02,940 --> 00:43:03,940
Back in university.

789
00:43:03,940 --> 00:43:07,400
So you're saying, even back then,

790
00:43:07,490 --> 00:43:09,050
she's had a crush on me?

791
00:43:09,140 --> 00:43:12,950
You must do better than just
buying me a nice meal.

792
00:43:14,320 --> 00:43:15,330
This is nothing.

793
00:43:15,420 --> 00:43:16,530
Whatever you want,

794
00:43:16,620 --> 00:43:18,270
just name it and you'll have it.

795
00:43:18,270 --> 00:43:19,790
But you have to answer me.
